Fuck it!

04:09.461 --> 04:10.962
Fuck!

04:16.218 --> 04:17.135
Fuck.

04:29.146 --> 04:31.440
Fuck.

04:40.740 --> 04:41.825
Fuck.

04:41.991 --> 04:43.284
Fuckity fuck!

04:48.581 --> 04:50.458
Bugger.

05:00.008 --> 05:02.010
Hello, Charles.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.819
There's a greatness to your lateness.

05:20.027 --> 05:22.738
It's not achieved without real suffering.

05:24.531 --> 05:26.366
I am so sorry.

05:26.533 --> 05:30.120
I'll be killing myself after the service,
if that's any consolation.

05:30.370 --> 05:34.541
- Doesn't matter. Tom was standing by.
- Thanks, Tom. You're a saint.

05:34.833 --> 05:36.709
Disastrous haircut.

05:41.213 --> 05:43.799
- You haven't forgotten the rings?
- No.

06:03.026 --> 06:05.612
Hate people being late. Hate it.

06:16.330 --> 06:18.332
Here we go.

06:40.352 --> 06:42.687
Oh, isn't she lovely!

06:42.896 --> 06:46.316
Scarlett, you're blind.
She looks like a big meringue.

06:54.073 --> 06:57.910
Dear friends, what a joy it is
to welcome you to our church...

06:58.160 --> 07:02.164
...on this wonderful day
for Angus and Laura.

07:02.415 --> 07:07.627
Before we start the service,
let us all join together in the first hymn.

08:10.853 --> 08:12.646
Scarlett.

08:15.733 --> 08:19.528
Dearly beloved, we are gathered
together here in the sight of God

08:19.779 --> 08:21.905
...and in the face of this congregation...

08:22.113 --> 08:26.159
...to join together this man
and this woman in holy matrimony,...

08:26.451 --> 08:30.789
...which is an honourable estate,
instituted in the time of man's innocency.

08:31.039 --> 08:32.248
Back in a sec.

08:32.414 --> 08:34.793
If any man can show
any just cause or impediment...

08:35.001 --> 08:37.419
...why they may not be
lawfully joined together,...

08:37.503 --> 08:40.714
...let him speak now
or for ever hold his peace.

08:42.006 --> 08:44.927
Do you promise to love her, comfort her,...

08:45.010 --> 08:48.013
...honour and keep her,
in sickness and in health,...

08:48.263 --> 08:52.058
...and, forsaking all others,
keep thee only unto her...

08:52.350 --> 08:55.144
...for as long as ye both shall live?
- I do.

08:55.686 --> 08:57.480
To love and to cherish...

08:57.563 --> 09:00.441
...till death us do part.
- till death us do part.

09:00.650 --> 09:05.363
- And thereto I pledge thee my troth.
- And thereto I pledge thee my troth.

09:07.114 --> 09:09.116
Do you have the ring?

09:16.206 --> 09:20.793
- With this ring, I thee wed.
- With this ring, I thee wed.

09:21.085 --> 09:23.295
With my body, I thee worship.

09:24.463 --> 09:26.841
With my body, I thee worship.

09:27.091 --> 09:29.760
And with all my worldly goods
I do thee endow.

09:30.302 --> 09:33.889
And with all my worldly goods
I thee endow.

09:39.978 --> 09:44.274
"If I speak with the tongues of men
and of angels, but have not love,...

09:44.566 --> 09:48.069
...I am become as sounding brass,
or a clanging cymbal."

09:48.194 --> 09:49.320
Good point.

10:46.999 --> 10:50.502
- Great hat.
- Thanks. I bought it specially.

10:54.839 --> 10:56.674
There.

11:03.681 --> 11:06.392
Right. Get in position, please.

11:06.934 --> 11:09.019
Thank you. Smile.

11:09.561 --> 11:13.982
- Splendid, I thought. What did you think?
- I thought splendid. What did you think?

11:14.233 --> 11:15.442
Splendid, I thought.

11:15.609 --> 11:18.028
Scarlotta, fabulous dress!

11:18.237 --> 11:20.571
The ecclesiastical purple
and the pagan orange...

11:20.780 --> 11:22.907
...symbolising the symbiosis in marriage...

11:23.074 --> 11:25.576
...between the heathen
and Christian traditions?

11:25.785 --> 11:27.578
That's right.

11:28.079 --> 11:30.790
Lovely. And again.

11:32.375 --> 11:35.877
- Any idea who the girl in the black hat is?
- Name's Carrie.

11:36.128 --> 11:38.839
- She's pretty.
- American.

11:39.172 --> 11:40.090
Interesting.

11:40.215 --> 11:42.300
Slut.

11:42.509 --> 11:44.428
Really?

11:44.928 --> 11:47.222
Used to work at Vogue.
Lives in America now.

11:47.431 --> 11:49.933
Only goes out with
very glamorous people.

11:50.142 --> 11:52.518
Quite out of your league.

11:53.436 --> 11:55.438
Well, that's a relief. Thanks.

11:55.813 --> 11:59.817
- See you there.
- Off you go.

12:00.943 --> 12:03.320
Right. Reception.

12:07.407 --> 12:09.409
Bye!

12:15.749 --> 12:18.460
Anyone else tread in a cowpat?

12:18.585 --> 12:21.295
No, thought not. See you in a mo.

12:21.503 --> 12:24.882
Do you think I'd hate him as much
if he wasn't my brother?

12:26.717 --> 12:31.096
Don't want to blow my chances
for romance by smelling of dung.

12:35.224 --> 12:38.853
I never know what to say
in these wretched line-ups.

12:39.103 --> 12:43.024
It's a cinch. Just give a big, warm hug
and say the bride looks pregnant.

12:43.274 --> 12:47.612
- Or go for "You must be very proud".
- Heaven preserve us.

12:48.112 --> 12:50.405
- You must be very proud.
- Indeed.

12:51.323 --> 12:53.116
- Hello.
- Hello.

12:53.283 --> 12:54.493
Hello.

13:01.333 --> 13:04.503
Hi. We've met. It's Richard Maples.

13:06.003 --> 13:08.005
Bastard.

13:14.762 --> 13:16.180
Hello, Bern.

13:16.347 --> 13:17.640
Two, please.

13:17.807 --> 13:20.892
- You have fun.
- Take care.

13:23.978 --> 13:26.272
- Hello.
- Hi.

13:27.607 --> 13:30.902
- Do you want one of these?
- Thank you.

13:31.152 --> 13:32.862
- I...
- Hello, Charles.

13:33.029 --> 13:35.948
Hello, dear John.
How are you? How are you?

13:36.156 --> 13:38.909
- Good. This is...
- Carrie.

13:39.159 --> 13:41.870
- Delighted. I'm John.
- Hi, John.

13:43.664 --> 13:46.750
- How's your gorgeous girlfriend?
- She's no longer my girlfriend.

13:47.084 --> 13:49.420
Ah, dear. I wouldn't get
too gloomy about it.

13:49.586 --> 13:53.923
Rumour has it she never stopped bonking
Toby de Lisle in case you didn't work out.

13:54.173 --> 13:57.260
She is now my wife.

13:57.510 --> 14:00.013
Excellent. Congratulations.

14:00.263 --> 14:02.265
Excuse me.

14:03.141 --> 14:05.642
Any kids or anything, John?

14:05.892 --> 14:09.396
Do we hear the patter of tiny feet?

14:10.689 --> 14:12.149
No.

14:12.190 --> 14:16.194
Well, there's plenty of time for that,
isn't there? No hurry.

14:25.870 --> 14:27.872
Hi. How are you?

14:43.386 --> 14:46.306
- My name's Fiona.
- I'm Gerald.

14:47.682 --> 14:51.185
- What do you do?
- I'm training to be a priest.

14:51.393 --> 14:53.312
Good Lord!

14:53.896 --> 14:56.523
- Do you do weddings?
- No, not yet.

14:56.648 --> 14:59.234
I will, of course. Jolly nerve-racking.

14:59.443 --> 15:02.654
Yes, rather like the first time one has sex.

15:04.572 --> 15:06.449
Well, I suppose so.

15:06.657 --> 15:10.870
Though rather less messy, of course,
and far less call for condoms.

15:34.892 --> 15:39.105
- Who's that boy over there in the grey?
- His name's David.

15:39.897 --> 15:42.316
Something of a dish, isn't he?

15:42.525 --> 15:44.652
Well, I've always thought so.

15:44.819 --> 15:47.530
- Why are they...?
- The dish can't hear.

15:49.864 --> 15:50.865
Gosh.

15:50.990 --> 15:55.286
Yeah, silent but deadly attractive.

15:56.204 --> 15:58.081
Bang, bang, bang. That's it.

15:58.248 --> 16:00.959
Into the marquee, please.
Dinner is served.

16:03.670 --> 16:07.589
- How do you do?
- Hello. Tom. Splendid to meet you.

16:07.840 --> 16:09.842
Very exciting.

16:21.936 --> 16:23.354
Hi.

16:24.647 --> 16:29.360
My name's Scarlett. Don't let me
drink too much cos I'll get really flirty.

16:31.237 --> 16:35.699
- How do you do? My name's Charles.
- Don't be ridiculous.

16:35.907 --> 16:41.413
- Charles died 20 years ago.
- Must be a different Charles, I think.

16:41.747 --> 16:44.041
Are you telling me
I don't know my own brother?

16:44.249 --> 16:45.250
No.

17:01.682 --> 17:05.560
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm sorry to drag you from your desserts.

17:05.852 --> 17:09.731
There are just one or two little things
I feel I should say, as best man.

17:09.981 --> 17:14.694
This is only the second time I've been
a best man. I hope I did OK that time.

17:14.986 --> 17:18.198
The couple in question
are at least still talking to me.

17:19.906 --> 17:23.702
Unfortunately, they're not
actually talking to each other.

17:23.952 --> 17:27.289
The divorce came through
a couple of months ago.

17:29.124 --> 17:32.795
But I'm assured it had
absolutely nothing to do with me.

17:33.045 --> 17:38.549
Paula knew Piers had slept with her sister
before I mentioned it in the speech.

17:40.134 --> 17:43.429
The fact that he'd slept with her mother
came as a surprise,...

17:43.638 --> 17:51.186
...but I think was incidental to the
nightmare of recrimination and violence...

17:51.603 --> 17:54.398
...that became their two-day marriage.

17:54.648 --> 17:57.859
Anyway, enough of that.
My job today is to talk about Angus.

17:58.068 --> 18:00.779
There are no skeletons in his cupboard.

18:01.029 --> 18:03.532
Or so I thought.

18:04.532 --> 18:08.452
I'll come on to that in a minute.
I would just like to say this.

18:12.039 --> 18:13.541
I am,...

18:13.749 --> 18:20.296
...as ever, in bewildered awe of anyone
who makes this kind of commitment...

18:20.714 --> 18:23.717
...that Angus and Laura have made today.

18:24.342 --> 18:27.345
I know I couldn't do it and...

18:27.595 --> 18:30.473
...I think it's wonderful they can.

18:30.724 --> 18:33.809
So, back to Angus and those sheep.

18:38.022 --> 18:40.941
So, ladies and gentlemen,
if you'd raise your glasses.

18:41.150 --> 18:43.569
The adorable couple.

19:49.963 --> 19:52.466
I remember the first time
I saw Gareth dancing.

19:52.591 --> 19:54.968
I feared lives would be lost.

19:57.471 --> 20:00.474
She's a pretty girl,
the one you can't take your eyes off.

20:00.683 --> 20:03.394
Is it love at first sight?

20:03.601 --> 20:06.688
Good Lord, no!
It's the bloke she's dancing with.

20:06.938 --> 20:11.651
I played rugby with him at school.
I'm wondering what position he played.

20:13.027 --> 20:15.822
Though, let's say,
for the sake of argument,...

20:16.030 --> 20:19.199
...one did take a fancy
to someone at a wedding.

20:19.449 --> 20:22.369
Do you think there really
are people who can say...

20:22.577 --> 20:26.289
..."Hi, babe. My name's Charles.
This is your lucky night"?

20:27.499 --> 20:30.585
- Well, if there are, they're not English.
- Quite.

20:32.379 --> 20:35.673
Three weeks is about
my question-popping minimum.

20:36.757 --> 20:40.386
You know I love you, Jean, don't you?
I love you. I love you.

20:41.137 --> 20:46.434
And, Mike, I've never met you before,
but I love you very much. I really do.

20:48.435 --> 20:51.146
Ignore her. She's drunk.

20:51.354 --> 20:54.941
At least I hope she is.
Otherwise, I'm in real trouble.

20:57.819 --> 21:00.447
- How's it going, Lyds?
- Bloody awful.

21:00.655 --> 21:03.574
Oh, dear! What's the prob?

21:03.657 --> 21:06.869
I was promised sex. Everybody said it.

21:07.161 --> 21:10.998
"You be a bridesmaid, you'll get sex.
You'll be fighting them off."

21:11.165 --> 21:14.793
But not so much as a tongue in sight.

21:15.544 --> 21:19.964
Well, I mean, if you fancy anything,...

21:20.840 --> 21:24.344
- I could always...
- Don't be ridiculous, Bernard.

21:24.510 --> 21:27.847
- I'm not that desperate.
- No, right. Of course.

21:28.056 --> 21:31.267
Fair enough. It's a good point.

21:48.199 --> 21:49.408
Bye!

21:50.993 --> 21:54.413
Have a lovely time! Bye!

22:25.818 --> 22:28.153
Where are you staying tonight, Charles?

22:29.780 --> 22:35.201
Scarlett and I are at some pub. The Lucky
Boat, something like that. Aren't we all?

22:35.535 --> 22:38.413
No. Slight change of plan.

22:38.663 --> 22:41.874
The others are coming back to my place.
Nansy's in residence.

22:42.083 --> 22:45.503
Might knock us up a plate of eggs
and bake over a late-night Scrabble.

22:45.753 --> 22:49.965
- I wondered if you'd like to join.
- Yeah! Thanks very much.

22:50.215 --> 22:52.759
- Is there room for Scarlett?
- Absolutely.

22:52.968 --> 22:54.928
137 rooms, actually.

22:56.471 --> 23:00.100
Right. Tommy, are you
the richest man in England?

23:00.350 --> 23:03.269
No!

23:03.477 --> 23:06.188
I believe we're about seventh.

23:07.106 --> 23:13.321
The Queen, obviously, and that
Branson bloke's doing terribly well.

23:13.612 --> 23:17.616
Well, excellent news.
I'll go and tell Scarlett.

23:17.866 --> 23:18.950
Yeah.

23:19.117 --> 23:22.454
That's unless you get lucky first.

23:29.753 --> 23:31.963
Hi.

23:32.172 --> 23:34.965
Hi. I thought you'd gone.

23:35.049 --> 23:40.471
No, not yet. I was just wondering
where you were staying tonight.

23:40.804 --> 23:42.389
Well...

23:42.556 --> 23:45.851
I was staying at some pub
called The Lucky...

23:46.143 --> 23:49.354
- The Boat or something like that.
- Boatman.

23:49.562 --> 23:52.690
Right. But now I'm going to stay
at some friends' house...

23:52.899 --> 23:55.318
...with some friends.

23:55.526 --> 23:59.238
Well, I think "enormous castle"
is a more accurate description.

23:59.489 --> 24:01.783
That's too bad,
because I'm at The Boatman.

24:04.242 --> 24:08.455
Well, it was nice not quite meeting you.

24:10.207 --> 24:12.584
- It was a great speech.
- Thanks.

24:18.631 --> 24:23.844
- Well, I'm going now.
- No! No, no. Don't go. We can meet now.

24:24.095 --> 24:28.307
- The evening's just getting going.
- We both know that's a big lie.

24:33.144 --> 24:34.562
Fuck.

25:00.170 --> 25:02.672
The castle beckons, Tom. Are you sober?

25:02.880 --> 25:05.550
Absolutely. Orange juice all night.

25:08.094 --> 25:09.220
Come on.

25:13.474 --> 25:14.767
Bye, everybody!

25:14.934 --> 25:17.145
All together now.

25:25.068 --> 25:27.070
Bernard!

25:48.089 --> 25:50.383
Tom, can you stop the car?

25:50.592 --> 25:52.594
Stop the car.

25:54.054 --> 25:58.266
Sorry. I just think
I might stay in that pub after all.

25:58.516 --> 26:00.644
Why on earth...?

26:09.693 --> 26:15.032
No, seriously. I'm doing some research
into pubs with the word "boat" in the title.

26:15.366 --> 26:18.576
- Oh, well. Please yourself.
- It's a silly thing.

26:24.582 --> 26:26.584
Right.

26:29.504 --> 26:31.506
Odd decision.

27:13.920 --> 27:15.839
Hello.

27:16.047 --> 27:18.048
- Hi.
- Hi.

27:18.924 --> 27:21.135
In the end there wasn't room for all of us.

27:21.552 --> 27:23.345
You said it was a castle.

27:23.554 --> 27:27.933
Yes, it is a castle.
It's just a very, very small one.

27:28.225 --> 27:30.853
Tiny, in fact.
Just one up, one down, which is rare.

27:31.061 --> 27:32.812
Drink, sir?

27:32.979 --> 27:36.107
Yeah. I'd like a glass of whisky, please.

27:36.316 --> 27:38.526
- Do you want...?
- Yeah, sounds good.

27:38.943 --> 27:41.279
- Another for the lady.
- Doubles, sir?

27:41.446 --> 27:43.448
Thanks.

27:44.615 --> 27:46.784
You here, too? How are you?

27:48.035 --> 27:51.622
- Hello. I'm fine.
- Haven't seen Carrie, have you?

27:51.788 --> 27:54.791
- Who?
- Carrie. American girl. Lovely legs.

27:55.626 --> 27:58.045
Wedding guest. Nice smell.

27:58.253 --> 28:00.839
- No. Sorry.
- Damn!

28:01.089 --> 28:03.799
Blast! I think I was in there.

28:05.885 --> 28:09.055
If you do see her,
could you tell her I've gone to my room?

28:09.305 --> 28:10.598
Yeah.

28:10.723 --> 28:12.725
- Your whisky, sir.
- Thank you.

28:12.933 --> 28:15.227
- And one for the...
- Road. Lovely.

28:15.519 --> 28:18.938
I think I might have one of those.
Do you mind if I join you?

28:19.105 --> 28:23.026
- No. It'd be lovely.
- Another glass of whisky and a cigar.

28:23.276 --> 28:26.905
Hold on. Make that a bottle.
We might as well settle in, eh?

28:27.113 --> 28:29.407
Let's see if we can push on till dawn.

28:29.616 --> 28:32.534
- Lovely wedding.
- Yes.

28:32.743 --> 28:35.746
I was at school with his brother Bufty.
Tremendous bloke.

28:35.996 --> 28:38.707
He was head of my house.
Buggered me senseless.

28:38.916 --> 28:41.085
Still, it taught me about life.

28:42.252 --> 28:44.755
Where do you know him from?

28:44.922 --> 28:47.840
- University.
- Splendid.

28:48.091 --> 28:49.968
Splendid. Yep.

28:50.885 --> 28:53.471
I didn't go myself. I couldn't see the point.

28:53.721 --> 28:57.225
When you work in the money markets, what
use of the nobles of wordsworth gonna be?

28:57.684 --> 29:01.187
Excuse me, sir. Your wife says
could you come upstairs at once?

29:01.437 --> 29:03.814
Room 12, in case you're so drunk
you can't remember.

29:04.022 --> 29:06.233
- My wife?
- Yes, sir.

29:06.775 --> 29:09.278
My wife!

29:09.486 --> 29:12.656
God! You are drunk if you can't
remember you've got a wife.

29:12.906 --> 29:14.700
Yeah...

29:15.409 --> 29:19.370
- Do you mind if I...
- No, no. Off you go. Best of luck.

29:19.662 --> 29:23.374
Lucky bachelor, me. I'll have another
search for that Katie creature.

29:23.624 --> 29:26.711
- Carrie.
- That's the one. Damn fine filly.

29:27.712 --> 29:29.714
I think I'm in there.

29:46.062 --> 29:47.896
- Hi.
- Hello.

29:48.063 --> 29:51.108
- Sorry about that.
- He was hard to get rid of.

29:51.358 --> 29:53.360
Yeah.

29:53.569 --> 29:54.570
So...

30:01.701 --> 30:07.915
Maybe we could just skulk around here
for a bit and then go back down.

30:09.626 --> 30:12.003
That's a thought. I don't usually skulk,...

30:12.253 --> 30:15.965
...but I suppose I could skulk
if skulking were required.

30:16.215 --> 30:18.634
Do you skulk regularly?

30:19.551 --> 30:25.724
No. No, I don't normally think of myself
as a skulker but...

30:29.102 --> 30:35.524
Well, why don't you come in
and skulk for a while and we'll see?

30:43.699 --> 30:48.745
I noticed the bride and groom didn't kiss
in the church, which is kind of strange.

30:49.037 --> 30:51.873
Where I come from, kissing is very big.

30:52.582 --> 30:56.795
Is it? Well, I think you're right.
We are probably more reserved.

30:57.087 --> 31:00.131
"You may kiss the bride" isn't
actually in the Book of Common Prayer.

31:00.382 --> 31:04.093
I always worry I'll go too far
in the heat of the moment.

31:07.680 --> 31:10.099
How far do you think too far would be?

31:10.307 --> 31:12.601
I don't know.

31:14.061 --> 31:15.771
Maybe...

31:17.730 --> 31:20.149
...that would be all right.

31:20.316 --> 31:24.821
- I think that would be fine.
- In fact, it might be a bit dismissive.

31:26.489 --> 31:28.491
Maybe this...

31:29.701 --> 31:31.910
...might be better.

31:34.121 --> 31:38.083
Yeah, I think it would be dangerous
to take it any further.

31:39.084 --> 31:41.086
I mean...

31:53.264 --> 31:55.891
That might be taking it a little far.

32:02.147 --> 32:03.565
What about this?

32:03.732 --> 32:08.528
Do you think the vicar would think things
had slipped a little out of his control?

32:08.820 --> 32:14.409
I think he might. This kind of thing
is really better suited to the honeymoon...

32:14.743 --> 32:17.119
...than to the service itself.

32:17.328 --> 32:20.122
Why do you think
it's called a honeymoon?

32:21.206 --> 32:26.503
