39:02.748 --> 39:09.254
...why I, Bernard Godfrey
Saint John Delaney,...

39:09.504 --> 39:14.217
...why I, Bernard Geoffrey
St John Delaney,...

39:16.177 --> 39:21.474
...may not be joined in matrimony
to Lydia John Hibbott.

39:22.558 --> 39:27.146
...may not be joined in matrimony
to Lydia Jane Hibbott.

39:29.231 --> 39:32.234
Lydia, repeat after me.

39:33.318 --> 39:36.529
- I do solemnly declare...
- I do solemnly declare...

39:36.738 --> 39:39.032
...that I know not
of any lawful impediment...

39:39.491 --> 39:42.661
...that I know not
of any lawful impediment...

39:42.869 --> 39:46.580
...why I, Lydia Jane Hibbott,...

39:47.039 --> 39:49.959
...why I, Lydia Jane Hibbott,...

39:50.209 --> 39:52.503
...may not be johned in matrimony...

39:52.711 --> 39:56.382
...may not be joined in matrimony...

39:56.674 --> 40:02.262
...to Bernard Geoffrey
Sidd... Siddun... Delaney.

40:03.012 --> 40:08.017
...to Bernard Geoffrey St John Delaney.

40:11.479 --> 40:14.898
I call upon those persons
here present to witness...

40:15.857 --> 40:19.236
I call upon those persons
here present to witness...

40:19.486 --> 40:21.780
...that I, Bernard...

40:28.662 --> 40:30.162
...Delaney,...

40:32.748 --> 40:34.750
...that I, Bernard Delaney,...

40:34.917 --> 40:37.503
...do take thee, Lydia Jane Hibbott,...

40:37.962 --> 40:40.965
...do take thee, Lydia Jane Hibbott,...

40:41.173 --> 40:44.175
...to be my awful wedded wife.

40:44.426 --> 40:47.345
...to be my lawful wedded wife.

40:47.554 --> 40:49.556
That's ri... That's right.

40:49.723 --> 40:52.183
May Almighty God bless you all.

40:52.350 --> 40:56.021
The Father, the Son,
and the Holy Spigot... Spirit.

40:56.271 --> 40:57.272
Amen.

40:57.439 --> 40:59.440
Bravo!

41:20.793 --> 41:22.003
Thanks.

41:22.170 --> 41:24.172
Coming, Bernie!

41:24.964 --> 41:25.924
Sorry.

41:26.758 --> 41:28.551
Sorry. Sorry. Sorry.

41:28.801 --> 41:30.510
That way?

41:30.677 --> 41:33.180
Sorry. Could you two...? Sorry.

41:34.014 --> 41:35.641
Sorry!

41:51.864 --> 41:54.158
I've got a new theory about marriage.

41:54.909 --> 42:00.580
Two people are in love, they live together,
and one day they run out of conversation.

42:00.914 --> 42:04.834
Totally. They can't think of a single thing
to say to each other.

42:05.085 --> 42:07.087
That's it. Panic.

42:07.295 --> 42:13.218
Then suddenly, it occurs to the chap
that there is a way out of the deadlock.

42:15.010 --> 42:17.888
- Which is?
- He'll ask her to marry him.

42:18.138 --> 42:20.057
Brilliant!

42:20.224 --> 42:24.645
They've got something to talk about
for the rest of their lives.

42:24.937 --> 42:28.566
So it's just a way out of
an embarrassing pause in conversation.

42:28.691 --> 42:31.276
The definitive icebreaker.

42:31.401 --> 42:35.572
- Tom! How's the speech coming along?
- It's pretty good, I think.

42:35.863 --> 42:39.075
Something for everyone. Tears, laughter...

42:40.868 --> 42:44.162
- Excellent.
- It's a very good theory, Gareth.

42:44.413 --> 42:49.209
There is another argument, of course,
that it has something to do with true love.

42:49.543 --> 42:51.545
Well, there's a thought.

42:55.799 --> 42:59.802
- Can I help you, sir?
- Can I have three brandies, please?

43:00.052 --> 43:01.470
Hi.

43:03.097 --> 43:04.181
Hello!

43:04.348 --> 43:06.851
- How are you?
- Fine!

43:08.352 --> 43:11.105
Sorry. I'm overwhelmed to see you.

43:13.190 --> 43:15.775
Look, don't go back to America. Please.

43:16.026 --> 43:18.820
- I'll be back in two secs, OK?
- OK.

43:20.822 --> 43:22.240
Hi, Fi.

43:23.116 --> 43:25.035
Those are yours. See you in five hours.

43:25.201 --> 43:29.204
- Something happened?
- It has. This is a bloody great wedding.

43:34.793 --> 43:36.086
Hi.

43:36.253 --> 43:40.090
Well, you look perfect.
In fact, you probably are perfect.

43:40.341 --> 43:43.052
- How are you?
- I'm really well.

43:43.260 --> 43:46.596
Charles, I'd like you
to meet Hamish, my fiancé.

43:49.766 --> 43:52.769
Excellent.

43:52.936 --> 43:55.730
How do you do, Hamish?
Delighted to meet you.

43:55.980 --> 43:58.149
Charming surprise
to find Carrie back in the country.

43:58.358 --> 44:00.359
Took a lot of persuading, I can tell you.

44:00.525 --> 44:02.945
Darling, I told James
I was going to get you.

44:03.153 --> 44:06.156
He'll think I've totally
lost control of you already.

44:06.365 --> 44:08.575
I'll see you later.

44:17.541 --> 44:19.919
How are you doing, Charles?

44:20.878 --> 44:23.381
Not great, actually, suddenly.

44:26.509 --> 44:28.510
I don't know...

44:29.553 --> 44:33.640
I mean, what the hell’s going on here?

44:33.890 --> 44:38.395
Why am I always at weddings
and never actually getting married, Matt?

44:38.728 --> 44:41.606
It's probably because you're a bit scruffy.

44:43.607 --> 44:46.819
Or it could also be because
you haven't met the right girl.

44:46.944 --> 44:49.280
Obviously, is that it?

44:49.446 --> 44:54.827
Maybe I have met the right girls.
Maybe I meet the right girls all the time.

44:55.077 --> 44:57.288
- Maybe it's me.
- Nonsense.

44:57.454 --> 45:02.375
My lords, ladies, and gentlemen,
dinner is served.

45:03.710 --> 45:06.629
Come on. Odds on,
you meet your wife at dinner.

45:08.131 --> 45:09.924
Yes.

45:20.350 --> 45:22.227
Oh, my God!

45:25.355 --> 45:27.357
Charles?

45:34.363 --> 45:36.574
- Hi.
- Hello. I'm Alistair.

45:36.782 --> 45:37.783
Great.

45:37.909 --> 45:41.120
- I believe you know Veronica.
- Yeah. Hi, Vee. Hi.

45:41.370 --> 45:43.371
Nicki.

45:45.332 --> 45:47.334
Great.

45:52.422 --> 45:54.925
Tell me, are you married?

45:55.592 --> 45:56.760
No.

45:56.927 --> 45:59.803
- Are you a lesbian?
- Good Lord!

46:01.430 --> 46:03.307
What made you say that?

46:03.474 --> 46:06.268
It's one of the possibilities
for unmarried girls.

46:06.393 --> 46:11.106
It is a bit more interesting than saying
"oh dear, just never found the right chap".

46:11.607 --> 46:15.401
- Quite right. Why be dull?
- Thank you.

46:19.739 --> 46:24.160
The truth is, I have met the right person,
only he's not in love with me.

46:24.452 --> 46:27.830
And until I stop loving him
no one else stands a chance.

46:28.080 --> 46:30.499
- Bad luck.
- Yes, isn't it?

46:32.793 --> 46:36.004
I was a lesbian once at school,
but only for 15 minutes.

46:36.213 --> 46:38.423
I don't think it counts.

46:45.596 --> 46:48.015
There are 400 different kinds of tea,...

46:48.307 --> 46:51.727
...and that's not including
all these so-called fruit teas.

46:51.936 --> 46:55.731
I took Veronica out to India at Christmas
to look at the plantations.

46:56.023 --> 46:58.817
- You and her went there once.
- That's right.

46:59.067 --> 47:03.280
Charles was vile. He insisted on
cracking jokes all the time I was ill.

47:03.947 --> 47:06.783
- Trying to cheer you up.
- You're that Veronica!

47:06.908 --> 47:09.619
Which Veronica? Charlie?

47:09.786 --> 47:12.622
- Remember Bombay?
- When Charles and I were going out,...

47:12.830 --> 47:16.500
...he told me he'd had this
interesting journey round India...

47:16.792 --> 47:20.087
...with Vomiting Veronica.
I think that was it.

47:20.296 --> 47:23.424
I don't remember ever mentioning it.
Maybe I did.

47:23.757 --> 47:27.760
Come on, Charles. I don't think I've
ever been out with anyone less discreet.

47:28.011 --> 47:31.931
- That's a bit of an exaggeration, isn't it?
- It is not.

47:32.181 --> 47:35.101
I remember you going on
about this girl Helena...

47:35.351 --> 47:38.521
...whose mother made a pass at you.
- I remember this.

47:38.813 --> 47:42.900
You couldn't work out whether it would
be impolite not to accept her advances.

47:43.191 --> 47:46.195
That's right. Mrs Piggy.
Helena was Miss Piggy,...

47:46.403 --> 47:48.864
...so her mother was Mrs Piggy!

47:49.364 --> 47:51.575
I think perhaps it was a...

47:51.783 --> 47:54.494
We've both lost a lot of weight since then.

48:01.292 --> 48:03.794
Great! The speeches.

48:04.003 --> 48:09.091
My lords, ladies, and gentlemen,
pray silence for the best man.

48:21.770 --> 48:25.440
When Bernard told me
he was getting engaged to Lydia,...

48:25.690 --> 48:30.611
...I congratulated him because all his other
girlfriends were such complete dogs.

48:33.405 --> 48:37.201
Although may I say how delighted we are
to have so many of them here today.

48:40.329 --> 48:45.124
I'm particularly delighted to see Camilla,
who many of you will remember...

48:45.416 --> 48:50.129
...as the first person
Bernard asked to marry him.

48:50.421 --> 48:53.841
If I remember rightly,
she told him to sod off.

48:57.803 --> 48:59.721
And lucky for Lydia that she did.

49:05.519 --> 49:07.396
It's very disappointing.

49:11.984 --> 49:15.278
We had the most adorable girl
at our table called Carrie.

49:15.570 --> 49:19.574
Apparently her fiancé's awfully grand
and he owns half of Scotland.

49:19.824 --> 49:23.035
- How are you?
- I'm stuck in the wedding from hell.

49:23.244 --> 49:25.872
Ghosts of girlfriends past at every turn.

49:26.080 --> 49:28.582
If I meet Henrietta,
the horror will be complete.

49:28.790 --> 49:30.208
Hello, Charles.

49:31.126 --> 49:33.086
Hello, Hen. How are you?

49:34.629 --> 49:35.630
Hen...

49:35.755 --> 49:39.342
Why can't you leave her alone?
Haven't you hurt her enough?

49:43.262 --> 49:46.849
Excuse me. I think I'd better be
where other people are not.

49:54.732 --> 49:55.649
Hello.

51:04.296 --> 51:05.881
Taxi!

51:13.888 --> 51:15.390
Good night, sir.

51:55.469 --> 51:58.889
It's all right. Oh, God! This is wonderful.

52:17.907 --> 52:21.827
Wait a minute. This is no fun.
I want to see my lovely husband...

52:45.641 --> 52:50.646
...who's a very bad bridegroom indeed.

53:06.077 --> 53:08.496
- Have you got a boyfriend?
- Yes.

53:08.663 --> 53:12.165
- What's his name?
- Dolph. He's good at table tennis.

53:12.457 --> 53:15.168
- What about you?
- No. Afraid not.

53:16.294 --> 53:18.296
Why not?

53:18.505 --> 53:20.674
Don't know.

53:21.424 --> 53:26.429
Because most of the blokes I fancy
think I'm stupid and pointless,...

53:26.720 --> 53:29.431
...so they just bonk me and then leave me,...

53:29.682 --> 53:33.477
...and the kind of blokes that do fancy me,
I think are drips.

53:33.727 --> 53:36.230
I can't even be bothered to bonk them,...

53:36.397 --> 53:39.400
...which does sort of leave me
a bit nowhere.

53:40.150 --> 53:42.569
What's bonking?

53:44.112 --> 53:50.034
Well, it's kind of like table tennis,
only with slightly smaller balls.

54:12.889 --> 54:14.974
So good!

54:27.110 --> 54:31.823
- I love my wife!
- And I love my husband!

54:35.452 --> 54:39.372
- Do you think we'd better get back?
- We could just wait a few minutes...

54:39.623 --> 54:41.540
...and have another go.

54:43.876 --> 54:45.669
Naughty little rabbit!

54:51.717 --> 54:53.594
Found it.

54:58.264 --> 55:00.683
Charles! Charles, we must talk.

55:03.186 --> 55:04.604
Right.

55:04.771 --> 55:08.775
The thing is, Charlie,
I've spoken to lots of people about you.

55:09.025 --> 55:12.736
Everybody agrees
you're in real trouble, Charles.

55:12.986 --> 55:13.987
Am I?

55:14.112 --> 55:18.325
You see, you're turning into
a kind of serial monogamist.

55:18.617 --> 55:22.913
One girlfriend after another,
yet you never really let anyone near you.

55:23.163 --> 55:25.082
On the contrary...

55:25.290 --> 55:28.292
...you're affectionate to them
and sweet to them.

55:28.501 --> 55:30.920
Even to me,
although you thought I was an idiot.

55:31.128 --> 55:33.130
- I did not.
- You did.

55:33.297 --> 55:36.384
- I thought U2 was a type of submarine.
- In a way, you were right.

55:36.676 --> 55:39.971
- Their music has a naval quality.
- Be serious, Charles.

55:40.179 --> 55:43.807
Give people a chance. You don't
have to think "I must get married",...

55:44.057 --> 55:47.853
...but you mustn't start relationships
thinking "I mustn't get married".

55:48.019 --> 55:52.107
Most of the time I don't think at all.
I just potter along.

55:52.399 --> 55:53.692
Charlie!

55:53.859 --> 55:57.236
Oh, God! The way you used to look at me!

55:57.486 --> 55:59.780
I just misread it, that's all.

55:59.989 --> 56:02.491
I thought you were going to propose...

56:02.700 --> 56:05.202
...and you were just working out
how to leave.

56:05.411 --> 56:09.248
- No. No, I wasn't.
- Oh, God, this is ridiculous.

56:10.624 --> 56:12.625
Hen...

56:13.877 --> 56:17.088
- Having a good night?
- Yes.

56:17.297 --> 56:22.218
It's right up there with my father's
funeral for sheer entertainment value.

56:22.427 --> 56:26.221
- I thought you'd gone.
- No. Hamish took the Edinburgh sleeper.

56:26.471 --> 56:28.891
I'm off now. Keep me company?

56:43.571 --> 56:45.573
Here, please.

56:46.491 --> 56:48.910
You want to come up for a nightcap?

56:51.078 --> 56:54.373
- You sure?
- Well, yes. I think we can risk it.

56:54.665 --> 56:58.376
I'm pretty sure I can resist you.
You're not that cute.

56:59.127 --> 57:01.213
Sorry... Yeah, great.

58:15.115 --> 58:18.243
Morning, Charles. Breakfast's up.

58:24.833 --> 58:27.126
What are you up to today?

58:27.334 --> 58:29.044
Oh, yeah...

58:30.045 --> 58:34.633
I'm taking advantage of the fact that,
for the first time in my entire life,...

58:34.925 --> 58:38.137
...it's Saturday
and I don't have a wedding to go to.

58:38.387 --> 58:40.680
All I have to do is not be late for David.

58:40.763 --> 58:42.765
I was going to go for a job.

58:42.974 --> 58:47.687
This new shop called Spank wants
a sales assistant. I think I'd be great.

58:47.979 --> 58:51.357
- They sell all this funny rubber stuff.
- No...

58:51.608 --> 58:56.612
Another wedding invitation,
and a list. Lovely!

58:56.945 --> 58:59.448
They say rubber's mainly for perverts.

58:59.656 --> 59:02.951
Don't know why.
I think it's very practical, actually.

59:03.076 --> 59:05.871
You spill anything on it
and it just comes off.

59:05.996 --> 59:08.707
That could be why the perverts like it.

59:08.957 --> 59:11.167
You all right?

59:12.293 --> 59:14.295
Yeah.

59:15.004 --> 59:19.217
It's that girl Carrie.
You remember, the...

59:19.467 --> 59:21.677
The American.

59:31.978 --> 59:34.397
Excuse me. Sorry to interrupt.

59:34.564 --> 59:37.692
- Do you have the wedding list for Banks?
- Certainly, sir.

59:37.901 --> 59:41.445
Lots of beautiful things
for around about the £1,000 mark.

59:43.239 --> 59:47.326
What about things around
the sort of £50 mark? Is there much?

59:48.452 --> 59:51.956
Well, you could get
that Pygmy warrior over there.

59:52.832 --> 59:54.834
This? Excellent!

59:55.042 --> 59:58.628
If you could find someone
to chip in the other 3,950.

59:58.837 --> 01:00:01.339
Or our carrier bags are £1.50 each.

01:00:01.464 --> 01:00:03.883
Why don't you just get 33 of them?

01:00:06.135 --> 01:00:08.847
Well, I think I'll probably leave it.

01:00:09.097 --> 01:00:12.099
Thanks very much. You've been very...

01:00:12.975 --> 01:00:15.978
- What did you get?
- Blimey!

01:00:16.186 --> 01:00:18.605
Well, I never!

01:00:18.814 --> 01:00:21.817
Nothing yet. I'm just, you know, deciding.

01:00:21.942 --> 01:00:25.027
- It's nice to see you.
- It's nice to see you.

01:00:26.195 --> 01:00:30.533
This present thing is great.
I should've gotten married years ago.

01:00:30.783 --> 01:00:33.661
- Anybody get the Pygmy?
- The young man thought about it...

01:00:35.079 --> 01:00:36.455
No!

01:00:36.497 --> 01:00:39.083
Just get me an ashtray.

01:00:40.458 --> 01:00:42.961
Are you free for about a half-hour?

01:00:43.211 --> 01:00:44.588
Yeah.

01:00:44.629 --> 01:00:47.841
I'm meeting my brother,
but I can be a bit late.

01:00:47.966 --> 01:00:51.261
Oh, good. You have
an important decision to make.

01:00:51.553 --> 01:00:55.055
- Now, you mustn't laugh.
- OK. Right.

01:01:02.480 --> 01:01:05.399
What do you think?

01:01:07.193 --> 01:01:08.777
Divine.

01:01:08.944 --> 01:01:11.738
Bit of a meringue?

01:01:13.198 --> 01:01:15.492
Don't worry. We've only just begun.

01:01:18.536 --> 01:01:20.955
What do you think?

01:01:22.081 --> 01:01:24.501
- You're kidding.
- But it would be wonderful.

01:01:24.667 --> 01:01:27.169
Maybe next time.

01:01:28.962 --> 01:01:31.340
What do you think?

01:01:35.427 --> 01:01:38.722
- I knew it.
- With a staff, you could look after sheep.

01:01:39.306 --> 01:01:40.807
Don't be rude.

01:01:41.891 --> 01:01:43.893
It's a bit sexy, this.

01:01:45.311 --> 01:01:47.104
Well...

01:01:47.230 --> 01:01:50.399
If I were your husband,
I would die of pride.

01:01:50.566 --> 01:01:52.568
You may be right. It is dangerous.

01:01:52.735 --> 01:01:56.530
There's nothing worse at a wedding
than a priest with an erection.

01:02:02.244 --> 01:02:05.247
It's strange thinking
you'll never sleep with anyone else.

01:02:05.455 --> 01:02:09.875
- You don't think you'll be unfaithful?
- No. Not once I'm married.

01:02:10.167 --> 01:02:13.587
I told Hamish I'll kill him if he does,
so I'd better stick to that.

01:02:13.796 --> 01:02:15.214
Quite right.

01:02:15.381 --> 01:02:18.342
Anyway, I reckon I've had my fair run at it.

01:02:19.135 --> 01:02:22.638
What is a fair run these days,
down your way?

01:02:22.847 --> 01:02:25.265
I don't know.

01:02:25.473 --> 01:02:27.475
More than one.

01:02:27.642 --> 01:02:29.853
Well, come on. Tell me.

01:02:31.020 --> 01:02:33.815
I've seen the dress. We have no secrets.

01:02:38.027 --> 01:02:40.028
Well...

01:02:40.904 --> 01:02:46.118
The first one - of course,
not easily forgotten - was kinda nice.

01:02:47.494 --> 01:02:50.080
Two... hairy back.

01:02:51.540 --> 01:02:57.253
Three, four, five... Six was
on my birthday in my parents' room.

01:02:57.795 --> 01:03:00.006
- Which birthday?
- 17th.

01:03:00.214 --> 01:03:03.092
- We've only reached 17?
- I grew up in the country...

01:03:03.301 --> 01:03:05.803
...lots of rolling around in haystacks.

01:03:06.429 --> 01:03:09.431
OK. Seven...

01:03:09.681 --> 01:03:12.684
Eight, unfortunately, was quite a shock.

01:03:13.852 --> 01:03:17.564
Nine, against a fence.
Very uncomfortable. Don't try it.

01:03:17.814 --> 01:03:18.815
I won't.

01:03:18.982 --> 01:03:22.486
Ten was gorgeous. Just heaven, just...

01:03:23.987 --> 01:03:27.281
- He was wonderful.
- I hate him.

01:03:28.532 --> 01:03:31.535
11, obviously after 10, disappointing.

01:03:31.660 --> 01:03:36.499
12 through 17, the university years.
Sensitive, caring, intelligent boys.

01:03:36.665 --> 01:03:39.501
Sexually speaking, a real low patch.

01:03:41.294 --> 01:03:43.588
18 broke my heart.

01:03:43.797 --> 01:03:46.299
- Years of yearning.
- I'm sorry.

01:03:46.508 --> 01:03:49.511
20... Oh, my God!
I can't believe I've reached 20.

01:03:50.762 --> 01:03:53.473
21, elephant tongue.

01:03:55.182 --> 01:03:58.769
22 kept falling asleep.
That was my first year in England.

01:03:59.436 --> 01:04:00.437
I do apologise.

01:04:00.479 --> 01:04:03.440
- 23 and 24 together. That was something.
- Seriously?

01:04:03.690 --> 01:04:05.901
27... That was a mistake.

01:04:07.110 --> 01:04:10.905
- Suddenly at 27 you make a mistake?
- Yes, he kept screaming.

01:04:11.197 --> 01:04:14.283
Very off-putting.
I nearly gave up on the whole thing.

01:04:14.408 --> 01:04:17.119
But Spencer changed my mind. That's 28.

01:04:17.370 --> 01:04:20.289
- His father, 29.
- With his father?

01:04:20.790 --> 01:04:22.416
30.

01:04:23.501 --> 01:04:25.502
31... Oh, my God.

01:04:26.461 --> 01:04:29.548
32 was lovely.

01:04:31.133 --> 01:04:34.553
And then my fiancé, that's 33.

01:04:35.804 --> 01:04:38.098
Wow!

01:04:38.306 --> 01:04:41.809
So I came after your fiancé?

01:04:42.351 --> 01:04:44.770
No, you were 32.

01:04:46.772 --> 01:04:48.566
So there you go.

01:04:48.649 --> 01:04:52.361
Less than Madonna,
more than Princess Di - I hope.

01:04:53.028 --> 01:04:55.530
And how about you?
How many have you slept with?

01:04:55.738 --> 01:04:58.741
Christ! Nothing like that many.
I don't know...

01:04:58.867 --> 01:05:01.870
I don't know what the fuck
I've been doing with my time.

01:05:02.078 --> 01:05:06.374
Work, probably. Yeah, work.
I have been working late a lot.

01:05:14.506 --> 01:05:16.925
I wish I'd rung you.

01:05:18.760 --> 01:05:21.180
But then you never rang me.

01:05:22.222 --> 01:05:25.933
You ruthlessly slept with me twice
and never rang me.

01:05:30.771 --> 01:05:32.648
Bollocks!

01:05:32.857 --> 01:05:35.067
Help me, please! Please!

01:05:47.829 --> 01:05:50.665
Carrie, this is David, my brother.

01:05:54.126 --> 01:05:55.503
Hi.

01:06:09.891 --> 01:06:12.977
I was just telling him
about you marrying Hamish...

01:06:13.228 --> 01:06:16.815
...and he said it couldn't have happened
to a nicer fellow.

01:06:20.485 --> 01:06:22.904
- Where are you doing it?
- Scotland.

01:06:28.075 --> 01:06:31.120
He says that's a beautiful place. Hilly.

01:06:32.287 --> 01:06:34.456
You should come to the wedding, too.

01:06:34.665 --> 01:06:39.794
I want lots of friends to make up for
the gruesome stiffs that Hamish knows.

01:06:40.837 --> 01:06:43.047
Well, you'd better go in.

01:06:43.548 --> 01:06:44.549
Bye.

01:06:45.007 --> 01:06:47.218
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:06:57.602 --> 01:06:59.604
Fuck it!

01:07:12.408 --> 01:07:15.536
Look. Sorry.

01:07:15.661 --> 01:07:19.165
I just... Well...
This is a really stupid question,...

01:07:19.415 --> 01:07:22.209
...particularly in view
of our shopping excursion,...

01:07:22.334 --> 01:07:25.837
...but I just wondered if by any chance...

01:07:28.047 --> 01:07:31.259
Obviously not, because
I've only slept with nine people.

01:07:31.509 --> 01:07:33.720
But I... I just wondered...

01:07:33.928 --> 01:07:36.431
I really feel...

01:07:36.514 --> 01:07:40.809
In short, to recap
in a slightly clearer version,...

01:07:41.101 --> 01:07:45.606
...in the words of David Cassidy,
while still with the Partridge Family,...

01:07:45.898 --> 01:07:48.901
...I think I love you. And...

01:07:49.109 --> 01:07:53.946
...I just wondered whether
by any chance you wouldn't like to...

01:07:57.158 --> 01:08:00.161
No. No, of course not.

01:08:01.788 --> 01:08:04.081
I'm an idiot. He's not.

01:08:04.290 --> 01:08:06.250
Excellent. Fantastic.

01:08:06.417 --> 01:08:09.628
Lovely to see you.
Sorry to disturb. Better get on.

01:08:10.170 --> 01:08:13.298
- Fuck!
- That was very romantic.

01:08:16.676 --> 01:08:20.846
Well, I thought it over a lot, you know.
I wanted to get it just right.

01:08:22.599 --> 01:08:25.309
Important to have said it, I think.

01:08:25.518 --> 01:08:27.853
Said what, exactly?

01:08:29.897 --> 01:08:36.112
Said, you know, what I just said
about David Cassidy.

01:08:40.907 --> 01:08:43.743
You're lovely.

01:09:36.042 --> 01:09:40.629
It was ordained for lifelong faithful
relationships and conjugal love.

01:09:40.796 --> 01:09:43.591
It was ordained
for the welfare of human society,...

01:09:43.841 --> 01:09:45.843
...which can be strong and happy...

01:09:46.051 --> 01:09:49.013
...only when the marriage bond
is held in honour.

01:09:50.055 --> 01:09:54.768
Into this holy estate
these two persons now desire to enter.

01:09:55.935 --> 01:09:58.938
Wherefore, if anyone can show
any just cause...

01:09:59.147 --> 01:10:02.567
...why they may not lawfully
be joined together in marriage,...

01:10:02.776 --> 01:10:04.778
...let him now declare it.

01:10:09.281 --> 01:10:10.949
Sorry.

01:10:11.033 --> 01:10:13.035
Please rise.

01:10:16.038 --> 01:10:20.834
Do you, Hamish, take this woman
Caroline to be your wedded wife...

01:10:21.168 --> 01:10:25.046
...and do you, in the presence of God
and before this congregation,...

01:10:25.338 --> 01:10:29.509
...promise and covenant to be to her
a loving and faithful husband...

01:10:29.801 --> 01:10:32.595
...until God shall separate you by death?

01:10:32.845 --> 01:10:34.722
I do.

01:10:34.889 --> 01:10:39.184
Do you, Caroline, take this man Hamish
to be your wedded husband...

01:10:39.392 --> 01:10:43.188
...and do you, in the presence of God
and before this congregation,...

01:10:43.480 --> 01:10:46.983
...promise and covenant to be to him
a loving and faithful wife...

01:10:47.192 --> 01:10:49.736
...until God shall separate you by death?

01:10:49.861 --> 01:10:50.946
I do.

01:10:53.489 --> 01:10:55.491
Fuck-a-doodle-doo.

01:11:20.807 --> 01:11:23.976
- How awfully nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

01:11:26.770 --> 01:11:28.772
Hello.

01:11:30.399 --> 01:11:33.068
You look beautiful.
Not a meringue in sight.

01:11:33.318 --> 01:11:34.903
Thanks.

01:11:40.616 --> 01:11:42.618
Blimey!

01:11:43.411 --> 01:11:46.539
It's Brigadoon! It's bloody Brigadoon!

01:11:57.507 --> 01:12:00.886
Dear old things, as you know,
I've always been proud...

01:12:01.178 --> 01:12:04.473
...that there's not a wedding ring
between the lot of us.

01:12:04.723 --> 01:12:08.184
Over the passing of the years,
it's beginning to distress me.

01:12:08.434 --> 01:12:12.271
I'd like to go to the wedding
of someone I really loved for a change.

01:12:12.480 --> 01:12:15.608
Don't blame me.
I've asked practically everyone I know.

01:12:15.858 --> 01:12:18.444
- You haven't asked me.
- Haven't I?

01:12:18.652 --> 01:12:21.655
Oh, Scarlett... Would you like to?

01:12:21.906 --> 01:12:24.491
No, thank you.
It was very nice of you to ask.

01:12:24.699 --> 01:12:26.493
Well... Any time.

01:12:26.618 --> 01:12:29.496
Quite right, Tom, quite right.
That's the spirit.

01:12:29.746 --> 01:12:32.540
Tonight, these are your orders.

01:12:32.749 --> 01:12:36.753
Go forth and conjugate.
Find husbands and wives.

01:12:37.003 --> 01:12:40.422
Excellent. What do you think, Fifi?
Spot a potential hubby?

01:12:40.672 --> 01:12:42.966
- Bugger off, Tom.
- Quite right.

01:12:43.050 --> 01:12:45.761
A toast before we go into battle.

01:12:47.429 --> 01:12:49.139
True love.

01:12:49.306 --> 01:12:51.683
In whatever shape or form it may come.

01:12:51.809 --> 01:12:56.896
May we all in our dotage be proud to say
"I was adored once, too."

01:12:58.272 --> 01:13:00.858
- True love.
- True love!

01:13:09.366 --> 01:13:12.369
Apparently, an enormous
number of people...

01:13:12.494 --> 01:13:15.789
...actually bump into
their future spouses at weddings,...

01:13:16.039 --> 01:13:17.999
...which is interesting.

01:13:18.083 --> 01:13:20.585
Yes, I met my husband at a wedding.

01:13:28.926 --> 01:13:33.556
Good Lord, I seem to have finished
my drink. If you'll excuse me.

01:13:38.309 --> 01:13:40.937
Hello. My name's Scarlett.

01:13:41.146 --> 01:13:44.149
Named after Scarlett O'Hara,
but much less trouble.

01:13:44.399 --> 01:13:47.318
- What's your name?
- My name's Rhett.

01:13:47.485 --> 01:13:48.903
No...

01:13:49.070 --> 01:13:51.364
- Not really?
- No, not really.

01:13:51.489 --> 01:13:54.450
- In fact, it's Chester.
- You kidder!

01:13:55.826 --> 01:13:59.037
I always imagine Americans
are gonna be dull as shit.

01:13:59.288 --> 01:14:01.290
Of course you're not, are you?

01:14:01.457 --> 01:14:04.042
Steve Martin's American, isn't he?

01:14:04.918 --> 01:14:06.837
Yes, he is.

01:14:07.004 --> 01:14:09.005
You're lovely.

01:14:18.181 --> 01:14:20.558
Hello, Charles.

01:14:20.767 --> 01:14:23.268
Oh, Hen. Hi.

01:14:23.477 --> 01:14:25.979
Look, I couldn't really bear a scene today.

01:14:26.229 --> 01:14:28.899
I know we've probably
got tons to talk about...

01:14:29.065 --> 01:14:31.777
Did I behave that atrociously last time?

01:14:32.778 --> 01:14:35.572
Well, you remember
the shower scene in Psycho?

01:14:36.198 --> 01:14:38.199
Scarier.

01:14:39.116 --> 01:14:41.202
God, I'm depressed, Hen! How are you?

01:14:41.285 --> 01:14:46.499
I'm cheerful. I weigh almost nothing
and I've got a divine new boyfriend.

01:14:49.001 --> 01:14:50.795
Perhaps we should've got married.

01:14:51.003 --> 01:14:55.799
No! I'd have had to marry your friends,
and I'm not sure I could take Fiona.

01:14:56.132 --> 01:14:57.717
Fiona loves you.

01:14:57.801 --> 01:15:01.679
- Fiona calls me Duckface.
- Well, I never heard that.

01:15:01.930 --> 01:15:05.225
Look, darling, come to lunch soon.
Give me a ring.

01:15:05.517 --> 01:15:07.518
Still cute.

01:15:11.730 --> 01:15:13.732
How's Duckface?

01:15:13.941 --> 01:15:16.151
Good form, actually. Not too mad.

01:15:17.694 --> 01:15:22.073
Ladies and gentlemen,
the bride and groom!

01:16:00.025 --> 01:16:02.445
You like this girl, don't you?

01:16:05.030 --> 01:16:07.031
Yes.

01:16:09.534 --> 01:16:11.494
Yes, it's...

01:16:12.412 --> 01:16:15.415
It's a strange thing
when at last it happens.

01:16:15.665 --> 01:16:20.170
And she's marrying someone else.

01:16:28.510 --> 01:16:32.723
How about you, Fifi? Have you
identified a future partner for life yet?

01:16:33.807 --> 01:16:35.809
No need, really.

01:16:37.268 --> 01:16:39.479
The deed is done.

01:16:39.645 --> 01:16:42.732
I've been in love
with the same bloke for ages.

01:16:43.524 --> 01:16:46.277
Have you? Who's that?

01:16:47.862 --> 01:16:50.281
You, Charlie.

01:17:08.631 --> 01:17:10.966
It's always been you.

01:17:12.093 --> 01:17:16.305
Since first we met so many years ago.

01:17:18.557 --> 01:17:20.726
I knew the first moment.

01:17:20.935 --> 01:17:23.853
Across a crowded room. A lawn, in fact.

01:17:29.692 --> 01:17:31.861
Doesn't matter.

01:17:33.029 --> 01:17:36.657
Nothing either of us can do
on this one. Such is life.

01:17:41.703 --> 01:17:44.706
Friends isn't bad, you know.

01:17:44.915 --> 01:17:47.251
Friends is quite something.

01:17:49.211 --> 01:17:51.213
Oh, Fi...

01:18:02.223 --> 01:18:04.600
It's not all easy, is it?

01:18:05.435 --> 01:18:07.436
No.

01:18:09.438 --> 01:18:12.149
Just forget this business. Not to be.

01:18:15.819 --> 01:18:17.904
Matthew, darling.

01:18:18.113 --> 01:18:21.323
- Where's Gareth?
- Torturing Americans.

01:18:22.158 --> 01:18:24.326
How thoughtful of him.

01:18:27.580 --> 01:18:30.458
Do you actually know Oscar Wilde?

01:18:30.666 --> 01:18:33.502
Not personally, no.

01:18:34.003 --> 01:18:38.548
But I do know someone
who could get his fax number for you.

01:18:39.132 --> 01:18:41.134
Shall we dance?

01:19:26.384 --> 01:19:28.970
Well? Any rings on fingers?

01:19:29.096 --> 01:19:31.306
Gareth, you don't know
how lucky you are.

01:19:31.390 --> 01:19:34.101
Finding someone to marry
is a tricky business.

01:19:34.351 --> 01:19:38.854
It's hell out there. Matthew's trapped
with an evangelist from Minnesota.

01:19:39.105 --> 01:19:41.273
Sweet Jesus, cast out the devil!

01:19:42.024 --> 01:19:47.029
My lords, ladies, and gentlemen,
please charge your glasses.

01:19:47.321 --> 01:19:51.199
First, and rather unusually,
we have the bride.

01:19:53.284 --> 01:19:55.703
Excellent. I love this girl.

01:19:56.538 --> 01:19:58.540
Thank you.

01:19:58.706 --> 01:20:03.503
First of all, I'd like to thank all of you
who've flown in from the States.

01:20:04.212 --> 01:20:08.757
As for the rest of you, I'd have thought
that lots of frightful Americans flying in...

01:20:09.049 --> 01:20:12.136
...was an excuse for staying away.
So I thank you, too.

01:20:16.223 --> 01:20:20.810
If my darling dad had been here today,
he would have been speaking now,...

01:20:20.977 --> 01:20:23.104
...and I know what he would have said:

01:20:23.271 --> 01:20:29.110
"Great dress, babe, but why in the hell
are you marrying the stiff in the skirt?"

01:20:31.863 --> 01:20:35.658
And I would have given him
the same answer that I give you:

01:20:35.949 --> 01:20:37.951
"Because I love him."

01:20:38.118 --> 01:20:41.621
As John Lennon said,
who died the same year as my dad,...

01:20:41.872 --> 01:20:45.584
"Love is the answer,
and you know that for sure."

01:20:50.921 --> 01:20:53.424
And one more thing.

01:20:53.632 --> 01:20:57.928
Someone told me here that, if things with
Hamish didn't work out, he would step in.

01:20:58.220 --> 01:21:01.515
I just wanted to say thanks,
and I'll keep you posted.

01:21:06.561 --> 01:21:07.562
Bravo!

01:21:07.729 --> 01:21:11.524
Now, my lords, ladies, and gentlemen,
Sir Hamish Banks.

01:21:18.156 --> 01:21:20.866
Anyone involved in politics
for the last 20 years...

01:21:21.075 --> 01:21:24.078
...has got used to being
upstaged by a woman.

01:21:25.537 --> 01:21:28.624
I didn't expect it to happen to me
on my wedding day.

01:21:28.874 --> 01:21:32.669
However, I must also say
that I'm quite happy...

01:21:32.961 --> 01:21:36.547
...to be upstaged by this woman
for the rest of my life.

01:21:36.798 --> 01:21:41.135
Is that some barracking at the back?
We politicians are used to that.

01:21:41.427 --> 01:21:44.305
- Shit! Find a doctor!
- Right. OK.

01:21:44.430 --> 01:21:47.225
First of all,
my compliments to the bridesmaids.

01:21:47.475 --> 01:21:49.769
You did your duties superbly.

01:21:49.977 --> 01:21:54.272
And obviously I intend to use you
every time I get married from now on.

01:22:00.487 --> 01:22:04.199
I want to thank
all those wonderful ladies of the parish...

01:22:04.449 --> 01:22:06.534
...who did the flowers in the church.

01:22:06.700 --> 01:22:10.830
The stern old building took on
a look of flushed youth today.

01:22:19.463 --> 01:22:22.966
I remember the first time
I laid eyes on Caroline.

01:22:23.216 --> 01:22:27.929
I thought to myself:
"If by any chance she's short-sighted,...

01:22:28.263 --> 01:22:31.558
...I might just be happy
for the rest of my life."

01:22:32.809 --> 01:22:35.602
I thought I could see my future
for the first time.

01:22:35.811 --> 01:22:41.024
It was a joyful one,
for years and years to come.

01:24:12.610 --> 01:24:16.823
Good morning, and a warm welcome
to you all on this cold day.

01:24:17.407 --> 01:24:19.991
Our service will begin in a few minutes.

01:24:20.200 --> 01:24:24.705
But first we have asked Matthew,
Gareth's closest friend,...

01:24:24.996 --> 01:24:27.582
...to say a few words.

01:24:36.048 --> 01:24:39.260
Gareth used to prefer funerals
to weddings.

01:24:39.427 --> 01:24:42.221
He said it was easier to get enthusiastic...

01:24:42.304 --> 01:24:47.226
...about a ceremony one had an outside
chance of eventually being involved in.

01:24:49.228 --> 01:24:52.272
In order to prepare this speech,
I rang a few people...

01:24:52.522 --> 01:24:57.110
...to get a general picture of how Gareth
was regarded by those who met him.

01:24:58.778 --> 01:25:02.574
"Fat" seems to have been a word
people most connected with him.

01:25:04.825 --> 01:25:07.828
"Terribly rude" also rang a lot of bells.

01:25:09.663 --> 01:25:15.461
So "very fat" and "very rude" seems
to have been the stranger's viewpoint.

01:25:15.669 --> 01:25:19.381
But some of you have rung me
and let me know that you loved him,...

01:25:19.756 --> 01:25:23.259
...which I know he would have been
thrilled to hear.

01:25:23.384 --> 01:25:28.556
You remember his fabulous hospitality,
his strange experimental cooking.

01:25:31.100 --> 01:25:35.896
The recipe for duck á la banana
fortunately goes with him to his grave.

01:25:37.564 --> 01:25:42.569
Most of all, you tell me of
his enormous capacity for joy.

01:25:42.986 --> 01:25:48.075
And, when joyful,
for highly vocal drunkenness.

01:25:51.577 --> 01:25:54.747
I hope joyful is how
you will remember him.

01:25:56.957 --> 01:25:59.752
Not stuck in a box in a church.

01:26:03.005 --> 01:26:07.300
Pick your favourite of his waistcoats
and remember him that way.

01:26:07.592 --> 01:26:11.388
The most splendid, replete,...

01:26:12.722 --> 01:26:15.725
...big-hearted...

01:26:16.351 --> 01:26:18.978
...weak-hearted, as it turned out -...

01:26:19.145 --> 01:26:22.147
...and jolly bugger most of us ever met.

01:26:25.317 --> 01:26:28.445
As for me, you may ask
how I will remember him.

01:26:30.030 --> 01:26:32.449
What I thought of him.

01:26:36.619 --> 01:26:39.580
Unfortunately, there I run out of words.

01:26:42.917 --> 01:26:45.128
Forgive me
if I turn from my own feelings...

01:26:45.336 --> 01:26:50.549
...to the words of another
splendid bugger, W.H. Auden.

01:26:51.508 --> 01:26:54.010
This is actually what I want to say:

01:26:57.347 --> 01:27:00.726
Stop all the clocks, cut off the telephone,

01:27:02.686 --> 01:27:05.896
Prevent the dog from barking
with a juicy bone,

01:27:08.107 --> 01:27:11.193
Silence the pianos
and with muffled drum

01:27:11.402 --> 01:27:15.781
Bring out the coffin,
let the mourners come.

01:27:17.575 --> 01:27:20.285
Let the aeroplanes circle
moaning overhead

01:27:20.368 --> 01:27:24.581
Scribbling on the sky the message
He Is Dead.

01:27:26.750 --> 01:27:30.253
Put crepe bows round the white necks
of the public doves,

01:27:32.505 --> 01:27:35.883
Let traffic policemen
wear black cotton gloves.

01:27:37.676 --> 01:27:41.680
He was my North, my South,
my East and West.

01:27:43.348 --> 01:27:46.518
My working week and my Sunday rest,

01:27:48.312 --> 01:27:52.315
My noon, my midnight, my talk, my song;

01:27:55.234 --> 01:27:58.321
I thought that love would last for ever:

01:27:59.405 --> 01:28:01.574
I was wrong.

01:28:04.910 --> 01:28:07.079
The stars are not wanted now:

01:28:08.663 --> 01:28:11.083
Put out every one;

01:28:12.334 --> 01:28:15.337
Pack up the moon and dismantle the sun;

01:28:18.173 --> 01:28:20.925
Pour away the ocean
and sweep up the wood.

01:28:22.927 --> 01:28:26.138
For nothing now
can ever come to any good.

01:29:03.298 --> 01:29:08.010
It was good of you to come. Must have
been the shortest honeymoon in history.

01:29:08.219 --> 01:29:10.722
No, it's fine. We'll do it some other time.

01:29:15.810 --> 01:29:18.021
You know, what you said in the street...

01:29:18.229 --> 01:29:21.440
- Yes, I'm sorry about that.
- No, I liked it.

01:29:21.648 --> 01:29:24.359
I liked you saying it.

01:29:34.869 --> 01:29:37.872
Charlie, I'll take Scarlett home, all right?

01:29:39.373 --> 01:29:41.375
Darling Fi.

01:29:49.799 --> 01:29:51.593
Walk, Charlie?

01:29:51.801 --> 01:29:54.387
Yeah. Yeah, that would be grand.

01:29:57.849 --> 01:30:01.436
Never felt like that.
I mean, something vaguely similar,...

01:30:01.686 --> 01:30:04.521
...for Jilly, when I was young.

01:30:04.730 --> 01:30:06.523
Jilly?

01:30:06.690 --> 01:30:08.692
Labrador.

01:30:10.110 --> 01:30:12.404
Yes, it's odd, isn't it?

01:30:12.613 --> 01:30:15.115
All these years
we've been single and proud of it...

01:30:15.366 --> 01:30:19.952
...and never noticed that two of us were,
in effect, married all this time.

01:30:20.244 --> 01:30:22.580
Traitors in our midst.

01:30:26.417 --> 01:30:30.296
You know, I think death is hardest
for the parents, don't you?

01:30:30.588 --> 01:30:32.882
I hope I die before my children.

01:30:33.091 --> 01:30:34.466
Tom...

01:30:34.549 --> 01:30:37.427
There's one thing I find really...

01:30:40.764 --> 01:30:44.476
Well... It's your total confidence
that you will get married.

01:30:44.726 --> 01:30:48.646
I mean, what if
you never find the right girl?

01:30:48.938 --> 01:30:49.939
Sorry?

01:30:50.064 --> 01:30:53.359
Surely, if that service shows anything,...

01:30:53.609 --> 01:30:56.821
...it shows that there is such a thing
as a perfect match.

01:30:57.029 --> 01:31:01.951
If we can't be like Gareth and Matthew,
then maybe we should just let it go.

01:31:02.993 --> 01:31:05.495
Some of us are not gonna get married.

01:31:05.704 --> 01:31:08.123
Well, I don't know, Charlie.

01:31:08.957 --> 01:31:13.545
The truth is, unlike you,
I never expected the thunderbolt.

01:31:14.754 --> 01:31:18.383
I always just hoped that I'd meet
some nice, friendly girl,...

01:31:18.632 --> 01:31:23.220
...like the look of her, hope the look of me
didn't make her physically sick,...

01:31:23.554 --> 01:31:28.058
...then pop the question
and settle down and be happy.

01:31:29.768 --> 01:31:33.397
It worked for my parents.
Well, apart from the divorce...

01:31:33.980 --> 01:31:36.983
I'll give you six months
at the outside, Tom.

01:31:38.151 --> 01:31:40.570
Yeah, maybe you're right.

01:31:41.154 --> 01:31:47.660
Maybe all this waiting for
one true love stuff gets you nowhere.

01:32:04.800 --> 01:32:08.012
What the fuck is going on?

01:32:11.515 --> 01:32:15.186
I thought we'd better make
absolutely sure we weren't late.

01:32:15.895 --> 01:32:17.605
Excellent wedding hairstyle.

01:32:21.399 --> 01:32:24.861
Matthew.
The best-looking best man in the world.

01:32:25.695 --> 01:32:29.866
Listen. Thank you for doing this today.

01:32:30.033 --> 01:32:32.243
Of course.

01:32:34.661 --> 01:32:37.665
I wish Gareth was here.

01:32:37.748 --> 01:32:39.958
Bet he does, too.

01:32:42.586 --> 01:32:46.090
I'm sorry we're so late.
The others are just parking the car.

01:32:46.340 --> 01:32:48.341
I thought we'd all go with Tom.

01:32:48.508 --> 01:32:52.220
- Late? So late?
- Yeah. It's 9.45.

01:32:52.428 --> 01:32:56.891
- 9.45?
- Yep. 45 minutes till "I do".

01:32:57.183 --> 01:33:00.561
Oh, bloody Tom!
I told him to set the alarm for eight!

01:33:00.770 --> 01:33:02.772
Fuck it! Fuck!

01:33:07.150 --> 01:33:09.861
- Scarlett.
- Hi!

01:33:10.112 --> 01:33:13.490
- You ready?
- Absolutely. Give me 20 seconds.

01:33:23.541 --> 01:33:25.042
- Time.
- Honestly?

01:33:25.209 --> 01:33:26.335
Yes! Time!

01:33:26.502 --> 01:33:28.379
It's about ten to nine.

01:33:46.813 --> 01:33:48.814
Bastards.

01:33:51.066 --> 01:33:53.777
Jessica, stop jumping
up and down, please.

01:33:57.448 --> 01:34:00.075
One, two, three, smile!

01:34:03.286 --> 01:34:07.915
- This is splendid tuck.
- Yes, I think I might say a little word.

01:34:08.207 --> 01:34:12.795
As you know, I've been a close observer
of Charles's love life for many years.

01:34:13.087 --> 01:34:17.883
But recently I'd started to despair and fear
that really he was married to us,...

01:34:18.175 --> 01:34:22.471
...except that we won't have his babies.
- I don't know about that.

01:34:22.637 --> 01:34:26.141
But it's all turned out splendidly.
The girl is sadly crazy,...

01:34:26.641 --> 01:34:28.518
...but perhaps that's why he loves her.

01:34:28.727 --> 01:34:33.522
I'd like to propose a toast to my Charlie
and his beautiful girl on this tragic day.

01:34:33.731 --> 01:34:37.360
- So, be happy and don't forget us.
- Thank you.

01:34:37.610 --> 01:34:41.322
- To Charles and Duckface.
- Charles and Duckface!

01:34:47.703 --> 01:34:49.996
- What do you think?
- You look divine.

01:34:50.205 --> 01:34:52.582
It does work, doesn't it? Yes.

01:34:55.835 --> 01:34:59.839
I'd like to thank Fiona for those
charming words about my future wife.

01:35:00.006 --> 01:35:04.093
I'd like to take this opportunity
to read a message from her to you all.

01:35:04.385 --> 01:35:05.969
This is exciting.

01:35:06.136 --> 01:35:10.140
She says "Any of you come near
the house, I'll set the dogs on you."

01:35:10.432 --> 01:35:13.060
I think that's a nice touch.

01:35:13.268 --> 01:35:15.145
Sweet!

01:35:15.354 --> 01:35:17.772
"Set the dogs on you"!

01:35:19.148 --> 01:35:21.359
John, hi.

01:35:21.442 --> 01:35:23.444
- John, you made it.
- Yes.

01:35:23.653 --> 01:35:27.365
I hope me damn sister turns up.
Not much of a wedding without a bride.

01:35:27.490 --> 01:35:29.117
Tom!

01:35:30.034 --> 01:35:32.453
Bit of a poor show
you not having a stag night.

01:35:32.537 --> 01:35:37.749
We did! We did... We didn't think it was
a very good idea in this day and age.

01:35:38.041 --> 01:35:40.043
Really?

01:35:59.854 --> 01:36:02.356
Fi, you do look lovely today.

01:36:02.564 --> 01:36:07.652
- I've abandoned my traditional black.
- Yes, so you have.

01:36:07.986 --> 01:36:10.780
From now on, I shall be
all the colours of the rainbow...

01:36:11.031 --> 01:36:15.118
...and fall in love with someone
who fancies me for a change.

01:36:15.410 --> 01:36:17.412
Darling Fi!

01:36:24.585 --> 01:36:26.295
- Look.
- What?

01:36:26.337 --> 01:36:29.131
Lipstick everywhere. That won't do at all.

01:36:32.592 --> 01:36:34.594
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:36:50.942 --> 01:36:52.944
Good luck.

01:36:58.033 --> 01:37:00.535
Hello. Glad you could come.

01:37:02.120 --> 01:37:04.288
Groom's on the right. Bride's on the left.

01:37:08.042 --> 01:37:11.629
- Groom on the right. Bride on the left.
- Oh, my God!

01:37:16.092 --> 01:37:18.760
I thought you'd gone back to Texas.

01:37:18.885 --> 01:37:20.970
Without you, never.

01:37:25.558 --> 01:37:27.560
Good luck.

01:37:31.439 --> 01:37:33.440
Bride or groom?

01:37:35.693 --> 01:37:37.653
Bride or groom?

01:37:37.945 --> 01:37:42.449
It should be perfectly obvious I'm neither.
Great God!

01:37:43.701 --> 01:37:46.328
- Bride or groom?
- Bride.

01:37:56.504 --> 01:37:58.631
Yes...

01:37:58.715 --> 01:38:00.425
I'm fine.

01:38:03.093 --> 01:38:05.512
I've a feeling we've met before.

01:38:05.595 --> 01:38:08.515
We have. About 25 years ago.

01:38:09.391 --> 01:38:12.728
I'm second cousin Harold's
daughter Deirdre. You're Tom.

01:38:12.978 --> 01:38:14.563
Good Lord!

01:38:14.771 --> 01:38:17.064
- So, you're family.
- Yes.

01:38:17.982 --> 01:38:21.986
- Only very distant.
- Well, yes, of course.

01:38:23.738 --> 01:38:26.824
You said you were bride?

01:38:27.074 --> 01:38:28.409
Yes.

01:38:28.534 --> 01:38:30.536
Well, do sit.

01:38:30.911 --> 01:38:33.330
Do sit here, Deirdre.

01:38:37.792 --> 01:38:39.836
Golly!

01:38:40.462 --> 01:38:42.255
Thunderbolt city.

01:38:43.340 --> 01:38:45.759
- Hello, Matthew.
- Nice to see you.

01:38:45.967 --> 01:38:48.844
- Hello, Charles.
- Bernard. How are you?

01:38:48.969 --> 01:38:51.555
- Exhausted, actually.
- Oh, bunny!

01:38:51.805 --> 01:38:53.807
- Charles.
- Hello, Lyd.

01:38:59.605 --> 01:39:01.607
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:39:03.358 --> 01:39:07.487
You look lovely. But then I always
did like you dressed for weddings.

01:39:07.945 --> 01:39:11.532
- And on time.
- Yeah. Extraordinary thing, isn't it?

01:39:11.908 --> 01:39:16.412
- How's Hamish?
- He's fine... I believe.

01:39:16.704 --> 01:39:19.039
- You believe?
- Well, yes.

01:39:19.206 --> 01:39:21.792
He wasn't the man for me after all.

01:39:24.628 --> 01:39:27.422
- You left him?
- We left each other.

01:39:30.467 --> 01:39:34.261
- When?
- A few months now.

01:39:34.553 --> 01:39:38.057
March was hell. By April, it was sordid.

01:39:38.265 --> 01:39:42.186
That's the last time
I marry someone three times my age.

01:39:42.478 --> 01:39:45.106
Charles, time to travel.

01:39:45.272 --> 01:39:47.273
Yeah.

01:39:49.150 --> 01:39:51.361
Coming. Good.

01:39:54.656 --> 01:39:59.244
- So why didn't you get in touch, then?
- I did think about it.

01:39:59.452 --> 01:40:03.539
I wanted to, but I was in a state.

01:40:05.290 --> 01:40:08.002
So, anyway, I don't want to keep you.

01:40:09.586 --> 01:40:12.006
And I'll see you afterwards.

01:40:12.172 --> 01:40:14.008
Yeah. Fine.

01:40:14.049 --> 01:40:16.051
Wait.

01:40:20.722 --> 01:40:22.724
I'll show you to your seat.

01:40:24.600 --> 01:40:27.020
Just showing her to her seat.

01:40:39.573 --> 01:40:42.075
Our timing's been really bad, hasn't it?

01:40:42.326 --> 01:40:44.828
It's been bad, yes.

01:40:44.911 --> 01:40:47.121
It's been a disaster.

01:40:47.330 --> 01:40:51.917
It has, as you say,
been very bad indeed.

01:40:56.797 --> 01:40:59.425
God, it's lovely to see you.

01:41:01.801 --> 01:41:04.012
Well, good luck.

01:41:04.220 --> 01:41:09.309
It's pretty easy. Just say "I do"
whenever anyone asks you a question.

01:41:18.484 --> 01:41:21.195
Could you just give me a sec, Matthew?

01:41:21.403 --> 01:41:24.490
Yes, of course. Freshen up at will.

01:41:43.841 --> 01:41:45.843
Dear Lord,..

01:41:46.010 --> 01:41:51.515
...forgive me for what I'm about to say...

01:41:51.848 --> 01:41:56.269
...in this magnificent place of worship.

01:41:56.561 --> 01:41:58.355
Bugger!

01:41:59.690 --> 01:42:01.691
Bugger!

01:42:08.114 --> 01:42:10.324
Can I help at all?

01:42:11.283 --> 01:42:13.452
No. Thanks.

01:42:13.577 --> 01:42:14.787
Sorry.

01:42:16.122 --> 01:42:18.623
Vocal exercises. Big church.

01:42:18.832 --> 01:42:21.334
Excellent. Often do the same myself.

01:42:21.584 --> 01:42:26.506
Not exactly the same vocab, obviously.
Rather more alleluias.

01:42:26.673 --> 01:42:28.883
I'll leave you.

01:42:47.025 --> 01:42:49.152
- Bride's arriving.
- Fabulous!

01:42:49.360 --> 01:42:51.738
We seem to have lost the groom.

01:42:52.322 --> 01:42:56.242
- Stall her and I'll see if I can find him.
- Roger. Wilco.

01:43:03.790 --> 01:43:05.792
Charles.

01:43:07.252 --> 01:43:09.630
It's good to see you.

01:43:11.923 --> 01:43:14.259
Yeah.

01:43:16.093 --> 01:43:19.305
Matt, what do we think about marriage?

01:43:20.306 --> 01:43:23.476
Well... Gosh!

01:43:23.643 --> 01:43:28.397
Well, I think it's really good,
if you love the person with all your heart.

01:43:30.066 --> 01:43:33.276
Well, exactly. Quite.

01:43:36.738 --> 01:43:40.659
All these weddings. All these years.

01:43:42.160 --> 01:43:45.372
All that blasted salmon and champagne.

01:43:45.497 --> 01:43:51.543
Here I am on my own wedding day
and I'm still thinking.

01:43:52.378 --> 01:43:54.588
Can I ask about what?

01:43:57.633 --> 01:43:59.510
No.

01:43:59.677 --> 01:44:01.678
No, I think best not.

01:44:02.387 --> 01:44:05.598
I'm sorry, there's a delay.
A problem with the flowers.

01:44:06.057 --> 01:44:07.141
Flowers?

01:44:07.183 --> 01:44:11.062
There seems to be a staggeringly
high proportion of hay fever sufferers...

01:44:11.396 --> 01:44:16.274
...and they're right next to the flowers,
so we're moving the congregation.

01:44:16.608 --> 01:44:18.902
Don't want the vows
obliterated by sneezing.

01:44:19.111 --> 01:44:23.282
Charles, would it be out of place
for me to say that time is ticking by?

01:44:49.347 --> 01:44:51.141
I think I've fooled them so far.

01:44:51.308 --> 01:44:54.394
When people think you're stupid,
they're less suspicious.

01:45:17.915 --> 01:45:20.084
Hello.

01:45:20.209 --> 01:45:21.794
Here you are!

01:45:21.961 --> 01:45:24.172
Ready to face the enemy?

01:45:26.049 --> 01:45:28.051
Are we?

01:45:31.553 --> 01:45:33.555
Yes.

01:45:35.015 --> 01:45:37.017
Excellent.

01:46:31.401 --> 01:46:33.403
Not so tight, Dad.

01:47:02.179 --> 01:47:06.559
Dearly beloved, we are gathered
together here in the sight of God...

01:47:06.767 --> 01:47:09.353
...and in the face of this congregation...

01:47:09.478 --> 01:47:12.857
...to join together this man
and this woman in holy matrimony,...

01:47:13.107 --> 01:47:18.612
...which is an honourable estate, instituted
of God in the time of man's innocence,...

01:47:18.945 --> 01:47:24.242
...signifying unto us the mystical union
that is betwixt Christ and his Church...

01:47:25.035 --> 01:47:27.996
...and therefore is not
by any to be enterprised...

01:47:28.246 --> 01:47:31.832
...nor taken in hand unadvisedly,
lightly, or wantonly,...

01:47:32.082 --> 01:47:35.377
...but reverently, discreetly, advisedly,...

01:47:35.628 --> 01:47:37.129
...soberly,...

01:47:37.212 --> 01:47:39.214
...and in the fear of God.

01:47:40.007 --> 01:47:42.593
Therefore, if any man
can show any just cause...

01:47:42.843 --> 01:47:45.428
...why they may not
lawfully be joined together,...

01:47:45.637 --> 01:47:49.933
...let him speak now or else hereafter
for ever hold his peace.

01:47:55.146 --> 01:47:58.775
I'm sorry.
Does someone have something to say?

01:48:04.821 --> 01:48:06.990
Yes? What is it?

01:48:09.117 --> 01:48:10.619
One second.

01:48:25.800 --> 01:48:29.220
He wants me to
translate what he's saying.

01:48:29.428 --> 01:48:31.221
What is he saying?

01:48:33.932 --> 01:48:37.143
He says "I suspect the groom
is having doubts."

01:48:37.560 --> 01:48:39.646
"I suspect the groom would like to delay."

01:48:44.567 --> 01:48:46.360
"I suspect the groom..."

01:48:58.539 --> 01:49:00.540
What's he saying?

01:49:03.334 --> 01:49:05.628
He says...

01:49:05.837 --> 01:49:09.841
...he suspects the groom
loves someone else.

01:49:12.135 --> 01:49:13.595
Do you?

01:49:13.720 --> 01:49:16.513
Do you love someone else?
Do you, Charles?

01:49:28.358 --> 01:49:30.026
I do.

01:49:36.073 --> 01:49:38.075
Get out of my way! Let me kill him!

01:49:48.376 --> 01:49:50.378
Blimey!

01:49:52.005 --> 01:49:54.299
At least it's one we won't forget.

01:49:54.424 --> 01:49:57.302
A lot of weddings just
blend into each other.

01:49:57.552 --> 01:50:01.138
- For God's sake!
- This one will stick out in the memory.

01:50:01.305 --> 01:50:04.099
For not actually including
a wedding service.

01:50:04.308 --> 01:50:06.936
Poor girl. No, I mean it. Poor girl.

01:50:07.144 --> 01:50:11.148
She's not my favourite person, but I think
what you did today was unforgivable.

01:50:11.440 --> 01:50:13.734
I can't bear to think about it.

01:50:14.859 --> 01:50:16.361
Poor Hen.

01:50:16.527 --> 01:50:19.948
- Though let's face facts.
- I'm sorry.

01:50:20.198 --> 01:50:23.868
If you weren't sure you wanted
to marry her today of all days,...

01:50:24.118 --> 01:50:27.205
...i. e., your wedding day,...

01:50:27.330 --> 01:50:30.832
...then it must be the right decision,
mustn't it?

01:50:31.750 --> 01:50:32.751
Quite right.

01:50:32.876 --> 01:50:36.880
It was a lovely dress.
I'm sure she'll find it useful for parties.

01:50:40.717 --> 01:50:44.428
- What did he say, Charles?
- Says he blames himself.

01:50:44.679 --> 01:50:47.265
- Absolutely not.
- No, you mustn't, David.

01:50:50.726 --> 01:50:54.146
- It's OK.
- No, no. If there's music to be faced,...

01:50:54.397 --> 01:50:56.732
...I should be facing it.

01:51:05.615 --> 01:51:07.534
Hello.

01:51:07.742 --> 01:51:10.745
- Hi! You're soaking. Come in.
- No, I'm fine.

01:51:10.954 --> 01:51:13.039
Comes a point when you can't get wetter.

01:51:13.248 --> 01:51:16.041
- OK, I'll come out.
- No, please don't. I...

01:51:16.292 --> 01:51:18.877
I just wanted to check you're OK.

01:51:19.086 --> 01:51:22.381
Not busy killing yourself
or anything, but...

01:51:24.133 --> 01:51:26.510
But you're fine, so...

01:51:28.304 --> 01:51:31.973
I shouldn't have come
to the church this morning. I'm sorry.

01:51:32.807 --> 01:51:34.809
No!

01:51:35.560 --> 01:51:39.856
Wait. It was all my fault.
I mean, I'm the bastard here.

01:51:41.608 --> 01:51:43.610
And it sorted out one thing.

01:51:43.693 --> 01:51:47.863
Marriage and me were very clearly
not meant for one another.

01:51:48.196 --> 01:51:50.198
It sorted out another big thing, too.

01:51:50.365 --> 01:51:53.285
There I was,
standing there in the church,...

01:51:53.493 --> 01:51:56.788
...and for the first time
in my whole life I realised I...

01:51:57.039 --> 01:52:00.374
...totally and utterly loved one person.

01:52:00.583 --> 01:52:03.002
And it wasn't the person
next to me in the veil.

01:52:03.210 --> 01:52:06.756
It's the person standing opposite me now...

01:52:09.008 --> 01:52:10.426
...in the rain.

01:52:10.593 --> 01:52:13.179
Is it still raining? I hadn't noticed.

01:52:13.429 --> 01:52:18.016
The truth of it is, I've loved you
from the first second I met you.

01:52:19.142 --> 01:52:24.940
- Not going away again, are you?
- No. I might drown. But otherwise, no.

01:52:25.273 --> 01:52:27.776
OK. OK. We'll go in.

01:52:30.945 --> 01:52:33.447
But first let me ask you one thing.

01:52:35.658 --> 01:52:39.161
Do you think, after we've dried off,...

01:52:39.703 --> 01:52:44.082
...after we've spent lots more
time together, you might agree...

01:52:46.042 --> 01:52:48.336
...not to marry me?

01:52:48.544 --> 01:52:51.172
And do you think...

01:52:51.339 --> 01:52:56.261
...not being married to me might maybe
be something you could consider...

01:52:56.552 --> 01:52:59.054
...doing for the rest of your life?

01:53:03.976 --> 01:53:06.395
Do you?

01:53:08.188 --> 01:53:10.399
I do.

